## MANDATORY ATTACK CATEGORY COVERAGE

**Every penetration test MUST cover ALL 14 attack categories.** Before finalizing your subtask list, verify each category has at least one subtask assigned.

<attack_categories>
**P0 — MUST TEST EVERY ENGAGEMENT (35% of exploitation time):**
1. Auth Acquisition & Bypass — default creds, registration, leaked creds (.git/.env/JS), JWT forgery (alg:none, RS256→HS256, kid injection), OAuth abuse, password reset poisoning
2. Sensitive Data Harvest — .git, .env, secrets, Swagger/OpenAPI, source maps, debug endpoints, S3 enum, exposed backups
3. SSRF + Cloud Metadata — test EVERY URL param/webhook/import/avatar/PDF generator. Cloud: 169.254.169.254, Azure IMDS, GCP metadata. Protocols: gopher://, file://, dict://

**P1 — HIGH PRIORITY (35% of exploitation time):**
4. IDOR/BOLA + Privilege Escalation — all endpoints with different auth contexts, horizontal + vertical privesc, mass assignment (role=admin, is_verified=true), UUID v1 prediction
5. Business Logic & Payment Manipulation — amount tampering, negative/zero amounts, currency confusion, fee removal, discount stacking, webhook forgery + signature bypass
6. Race Conditions / TOCTOU — HTTP/2 single-packet attack, double-spend, coupon reuse, withdrawal race, balance check race
7. Account Takeover Chains — password reset poisoning, OAuth redirect_uri manipulation, XSS→cookie theft, IDOR→email change, session fixation, MFA bypass

**P2 — STANDARD (20% of exploitation time):**
8. SQL/NoSQL Injection — GraphQL introspection→SQLi, NoSQL operators ($gt, $regex, $where), batch/alias brute force
9. API-Specific Attacks — GraphQL depth DoS, batching, field suggestion leak, REST version rollback, method override, parameter pollution, WebSocket CSWSH
10. RCE Vectors — CVEs, SSTI, deserialization, cmd injection, file upload→webshell, prototype pollution→RCE
11. KYC/Identity Bypass (fintech only) — document manipulation, liveness replay, session manipulation

**P3 — OPPORTUNISTIC (10% of exploitation time):**
12. Cloud/Infra Misconfig — subdomain takeover, S3 bucket enum, exposed panels, Terraform state
